
C++ console-based mini project that manages a list of people (name and mobile number) using an SQLite database. 
It demonstrates a combination of design patterns to structure the application cleanly and modularly.

✅ Project Features:
    Add a person
    Update a person
    Delete a person
    List all people
    Store data in SQLite database

🧠 Design Patterns Used:
    Pattern	                    Purpose
    Singleton	                Manage a single database connection
    DAO (Data Access Object)	Encapsulate DB operations
    Command	                    Encapsulate actions (add, update, delete, list)
    Factory Method	            Create commands
    Strategy (optional)	        Switch between display formats or validations


📁 Folder Structure

    PersonManager/
    ├── CMakeLists.txt
    ├── include/
    │   ├── Database.h
    │   ├── Person.h
    │   ├── PersonDAO.h
    │   ├── Command.h
    │   └── CommandFactory.h
    ├── src/
    │   ├── main.cpp
    │   ├── Database.cpp
    │   ├── Person.cpp
    │   ├── PersonDAO.cpp
    │   ├── Command.cpp
    │   └── CommandFactory.cpp


-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies:

C++17
SQLite3

Install SQLite dev libraries on Ubuntu:
sudo apt install libsqlite3-dev
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
